text: GS may stand for: ==Businesses and organizations== * Gold Standard, a Swiss- based non-profit organization that provides additional brand value to Carbon Credits * Goldman Sachs, one of the world's largest global investment banks * GS (Swedish union), a trade union in Sweden * GS Group, a Korean company that is a spin-off from the LG Group * Columbia University School of General Studies, one of three undergraduate colleges at Columbia University in New York City * Tianjin Airlines, by IATA code ==Places== * Gansu, a province of China (Guobiao abbreviation GS) * South Georgia and the G-protein coupled receptors * Gilbert's syndrome, a liver enzyme disorder which can cause elevated levels of serum bilirubin * Gitelman syndrome, an autosomal recessive kidney tubule disorder *
